reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Gold standard of Bluetooth speakers
reviews.author: bobby smith
reviews.content: The best bang for your buck Bluetooth speaker period. Sound quality is great, bass is good, and it’s super rugged and can hold up to drops, dropping in water or splashing, and even dirt and sand! The battery also lasts a long time and the speaker gets super loud, like this thing sounds better than my tvs built in speakers. My only complaints are that the eq isn’t super adjustable with only 3 levels for bass mids and treble. I wish there was at least a little loop or something built in to carry it too, and I wish the usb a port in the back was usb c. I also wish the usb c port was recessed with the other usb port and covered by the rubber flap so that sand or dirt wouldn’t get in it. Other than that, there’s really nothing else I could ask for in a speaker. If you’re looking for a Bluetooth speaker that’s super loud and high quality but still portable and pretty light I would definitely get the charge 5.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States October 9, 2023

reviews.title: 5.0 out of 5 stars Juicy Bloated Lemonade
reviews.author: Deth
reviews.content: Look I couldn't think of a good title...This little thing is amazing. I have been using Flip 5s for a while. Individually, those are great. But PartyBoost just doesn't work properly. Pops and thuds. Sound dropping completely. I'm no audiophile, and I honestly can't tell all that much of a difference in sound quality between the Charge 5 and the Flip 5, but I can say that I listened to music all day long using the Charge 5 as the base speaker for PartyBoost and had 0 issues with all the headaches that the Flips have been giving me.Basically, if you like the Flip, this has a bigger battery, marginally better sound, better IPX rating, and can be used to charge your phone in an pinch. It also uses Bluetooth 5 instead of the Flip's Bluetooth 4.2, which is probably a good chunk of the reason PartyBoost works better.Still no aux in, which is a mild bummer, but not a deal breaker. (The only thing I 'need' aux in for is currently using my Boombox 2, which conveniently has one!) No voice chat, which is a complete non-issue for me, but seems to be a pain point for a lot of folks.The case is nice, but I don't see myself needing it all that much for travel. I saw multiple people complaining about the speaker not fitting while others had no issue. I am fairly certain it is entirely related to what orientation you put the speaker in the case. Put it in the right way and it zips up no issue!Note: The Charge 5 does NOT come with a wall wart. You still get a USB A to USB C connector to charge it with, but you'll need to use an existing wall wart you already own. (I have seen complaints about this as well. But I have like 7 of them plugged in and another 10 or so sitting around as spares.)

reviews.title: 4.0 out of 5 stars An incremental evolution of an already strong product
reviews.author: Andrew Newman
reviews.content: The JBL Charge 5 is one of those "what you see is what you get" types of things. This is a speaker you might choose to use at home but it's "purpose" is to bring to an event where people want to make some noise and no "noise making" appliances are present. It allows everyone with a smart phone to play their favorite artist or mix and is loud enough to fill a room. Neither the dynamic range (noticable roll off on the deep bass end and a tweeter that is harsh until it breaks in and still sounds better from a distance) nor the accuracy are anything to write home about but that's really not the point. The point is to have fun, make noise and enjoy yourself. This speaker gets it done.One note, the Charge 5 is a bit "kidney" shaped vs the Charge 4. The supplied case that you get (for free) fits the Charge 5 much better if you turn it upside down with the "foot" facing up. The case provides a spot for the charging cable and a (user supplied) charging block. The device is already pretty rugged so it doesn't really need additional protection. The handle is handy.

reviews.content: Recently upgraded my Charge 4, my husband got my old one and I got the teal that I’ve wanted forever. I absolutely love this speaker, it’s small enough that I can take it with me anywhere and the sound is unbelievable. Mine lives in the bathroom because I need music in the shower, and the teal perfectly matches my bathroom. I take it downstairs with me during my workouts because I need music and I have no time for earbuds, I can control it from my watch and just focus on the burn. I’ve owned several Bluetooth speakers and they just don’t compare to this one,

reviews.title: 4.0 out of 5 stars Charge 5 is worth it, case not so much.
reviews.author: Ryan C.
reviews.content: JBL Charge 5 is amazing, with robust sound and durable material. The case, on the other hand, provides zero interior or exterior padding. It is just a thin hard shell that barely fits the Charge 5. Since it was the same price as the base Charge 5, I bought this one with the case, but I would not recommend buying this just because it comes with a nifty looking case. The case is a $5 value addition, at most. And if you want to really protect your device you will likely end up buying a better quality case than this one.
reviews.timestamp: Reviewed in the United States May 15, 2021

reviews.title: 3.0 out of 5 stars The battery dies rather quickly and there are sound issues.
reviews.author: Mitko
reviews.content: I always use it on low volume. The battery last for 10 hours or less. It feels like the battery drains at the same rate regardless if you are listening loud or quiet.Additionally, it does not sound good when connected to my Mac, it sounds better when connected to my PC or iPhone. Sometimes it interrupts the sound for a fraction of a second every few seconds when connected to my MacBook Pro.It does not accept sound through the USB-C port, it does not have AUX input, and does not have a microphone. The only way to connect it to anything is through Bluetooth.Overall it does what I bought it for, but not very well and nothing more.
